✨ Things You May Not Know About Me: ( Part 1 ) 👇

✨ I have an autoimmune disease called PCOS, 1 in 10 woman have it, and I work daily to keep myself in remission, It will be with me life long
 
✨ 2 Years Ago my parents got a divorce and it’s completely shifting my life especially living in Vegas where my closest family member is half way across the country. My family was extremely strong growing up, and I’m still navigating wounds, fears and overall understanding of it all.

✨I started braiding my hair because I was having extreme hair loss from my autoimmune disease. I tried to take something that was taking away  my confidence into something new fun and expressive.

✨ I have a lifestyle/clothing brand called @bittersweet_lifestyles that is truly my number 1 biggest accomplishment in my eyes. It has been on a pause for about a year due to life certain life events that made me need to step away for a bit, but I truly am feeling ready to dive back in. 

✨ I’ve lost 70+ pounds naturally, and have completely changed my appearance, confidence, and lifestyle.  I am indeed a Bad Bitch 💋

✨ I love to read 

✨ I tend to believe in others dreams more than my own 

✨ I believe my true life calling is to serve 

✨ I love y’all 

As I continue this dope ass thing called life, I want to make sure I’m representing ALL parts of myself on social media. I’m human, we’re all human, and though I have a lot of amazing life events to share and offer… I believe it’s important to create a space of vulnerability and authenticity, because we could just use another friend ✨ 

Happy Thursday Everyone 💫

Someone asked me the other day if I considered myself Plus Size…the question didn’t throw me off too much and to my surprise I immediately responded “yes I do”

They looked a bit shocked and said “ I mean to me you don’t look  plus sized at all” what makes you think that?

I honestly sat their in silence and after a while I said “idk I have Stretch marks  and curves and hips and have lost a lot of weight so I guess I’m plus size? 😅😂 

This was also for casting and booking purposes, so the question was totally warranted Yall 😂 

That day, I sat and thought about what I really thought about my body, my size, my confidence and If I felt “plus”
I also thought to myself , “what does that even mean” 💭

I’m not sure how to define me or if to define me, but I what I do know is that I am a proud , curvy , bouncy, strong, athletic, woman is proud of her skin, and her journey. I’m not sure what “box” my size fits into whether it’s…

✨ Plus 
✨ Curvy
✨ Thick
✨ Plump
✨ Full Figured or
✨ Sexy Af 😂

I represent and love alll that I ammmm :

✨Healhy, Happy, Growing and Flowing✨ 

Even though posting these types of photos TERRIFIES ME . I think I get to embrace my journey. The journey where I’ve been and where I am now ❤️

From ya curvy bestie, 

Dezi💛

🖤STEPS TO TAKE CONTROL OF THIS FEELING: 

1. Realize if the opportunity is in front of you, you’re ready: The truth is you will never truly feel “ready” if the universe has presented an opportunity in front of you that feels out of your comfort zone, it means it’s time to level up, you’re ready.

2. Recognize your accomplishments: It’s to start celebrating small wins, make a list of all your accomplishments, milestones met, habits formed, changes you’ve made. Reflect on the hard work and dedication you have already put in to get you where you are. 

3. Take action: when you feel like an imposter, take action towards the goal anyways. Leaders and “winners” that we look up too had the same fears, questions, and thoughts as you do… they just took action anyways ✨ 

4. Momentum builds confidence: the best thing you can do is start gaining momentum towards your goal, the second you even have the SMALLEST win it is positive reinforcement to keep going. Momentum is key, all you need to do is start. 

My entire life has changed in the past two years because I have changed my mindset, my framework of thinking, what I read, who I talk too….. 

I am hoping to share more of that with you guys. Let me know if this resonated ✨🖤 

Happy Monday , Get After It 🚀

I sang in front of the biggest crowd of my career and got in a hit an run accident in the same 24 hours. Some may say it was coincidence…. I believe their are no coincidences. 👇 

Here’s a real truth…. When you’re getting closer to your destiny and your purpose… when you’re starting to align, when you’re starting to gain your confidence… the world will.test.you. 

I got in an accident at 2am the night before my gig. I took a deep breath and said “Des… for the next 24 hours, let it go, enjoy your moment, be in your element and slay the damn thing. You can deal with this tomorrow. As that’s exactly what happened.

Not only that, I won my dispute today, my car is getting fixed, I will be in a safe rental, I got another opportunity from this event, and my high vibrations continue to flow. 

Stay strong friends, choose happy everyday, Train your mind to focus on the positive and Ride. That. Wave. 

Hope this resonated with someone today 💕✨

I believe I have finally fallen in love with being an underdog. 👉 I was writing my gratitudes this morning and without thought I wrote “ I am grateful for being an underdog” ✍️ I stopped for a moment and stared at that statement in its truest form. 

The truth is, NOTHING has ever come easy for me. I have had to work, and fail, and work and try, and push and prevail for every. Single. Thing. I have in my life. At times… I have been angry, at times…. I have had “why me” mentality. Now? I couldn’t be more honored to have had the journey I have had, and more importantly the person it has created. 

I’ve been blessed enough to have an amazing support system around me, but it is IMPERATIVE that I constantly remind people of where I came from. You know why? Because that’s actually life. 

Because I’m not an “overnight success” ( no one is, we have media to blame for that nonsense ) 

I am a woman who has learned..

✨Get Up earlier, Stay Up Later 
✨Keep Her Promises To Herself
✨Tired? Do it Anyways
✨What True Dedication Is
✨What True Discipline Is
✨What True Patience Is 
✨What Struggle Is
✨What Self Love Is 
✨What Sacrifice Is 

My body transformation, has led to my mental transformation, which has led to a life transformation that HAS JUST STARTED. 

As I grow older I truly believe our generation has less patience, less self love, less sympathy, less discipline…. 

May this be a reminder to truly EMBARK on the journey and learn to LOVE the journey, EMBRACE the journey and all that it has to offer. WORK HARD, Respect TIME, Respect YOU 🥹 

And if it’s hard? Even better, if you get through it, you will prove to yourself you can do ANYTHING. 

These photos are 75 pounds apart, an entire different mentality and lifestyle apart, and she is just getting started.

I am going through one of my hardest seasons of life yet, and I’m EXCITED to go through the storm because I can’t imagine what’s on the other side. 

…I’m just a normal chick from Maryland, with some wild dreams and alot of drive, you can do it too🧠 

I love y’all so much. Stay true to you and do the damn thing ✨

Here’s what I’ve come to realize 🫶 

- If you fall in love with the journey and not the outcome you are actually living life 
- Your 20s are the time in your life to TRY EVERYTHING, learn, fail, understand your strengths, values, and what you truly want to build out of your life 
- Focus on WHO not How 
- I am not a has-been but a will be. 
- Move out of your home town
- Failure is the best lesson we can ever have 
- Stop rushing, you’re doing fine
- Don’t Think, Do
- Loving yourself is step 1 ❤️

A BitterSweet Christmas Story🥹❤️🍋🍒 -( Touching on the gift of giving, imposter syndrome, and faith) Last night, I was sitting with a good friend, mentor, and big sissy to me enjoying the Christmas service before I head out for the holidays… ✈️ 🎄👇 

She was twirling her cherry necklace she was wearing ( that I had given her as a gift) 🍒 And She turns to me and says “Des, How many of these do you have in stock? I’m having a birthday party and I want to give everyone at my party something from your brand as a party favor. To support your small business and spread positivity and mental health awareness” 🥹 I literally didn’t believe her…. lol 

I said “ well, let’s pop over to the house and see how much I’ve got!!” 🥲 we head over to the house and she ended up purchasing every single hat I had in stock before the night was over. We made plans of the messages she could give her guests, a video I would make to send to everyone, and the power of giving and spreading positivity. Here’s the catch… 👇 

What she didn’t know, was that I had been battling imposter syndrome, and lack of worthiness, and honestly complete burnout for the past 2 weeks, & because of that, hadn’t launched my store online, out of fear, and negative thoughts.

👉I would look at my inventory everyday, ASHAMED, that I wasn’t being the business owner and leader I wanted to be, and the small fact that I’m literally sitting on cash flow, money for the holidays, and momentum. I ate me up everyday to look at this investment I had made and NOT follow through with it. 

She single-handedly, bought more of my brand that I probably would have sold in those two weeks, injected my business with cash flow, ignited a fire in my ass, reminded me of who I was, why I was doing this, and the TRUE power of positivity and giving. It literally felt like a Christmas miracle 🥲❤️

Thank you Irene for believing in me and my brand in my business, in times when I didn’t 100% believe in myself. 

The universe is always working, God is always working, there’s are miracles on the way you can’t even imagine. 

Life is truly bittersweet. Ride your highs and lows❤️ go sign up for the restock alert!! @bittersweet_lifestyles

Watch Me Have An Insane Breakthrough In Real Time 🥶🥲🤍(My First Ice Plunge Experience)👇

As many of us have seen the “hype” about ice baths, cold plunges, and the benefits of it all, I wanted to challenge myself to do this in the first week of the new year. It was something I have been wanting to try but have been too afraid to do. And that’s the beauty of it all 💫 

👉 I had a HUGE realization during this 5 minute process. One that solidified a way of thinking and belief I have had for years…… 

Who you surround yourself with is EVERYTHING. If you watch the video, at about a minute and half in, I wanted to quit. I started to get out… and If no one was there… my ass would be OUT. But something else happened. My friends encouraged me, they held me at a high standard they BELIEVED IN ME. And in turn it made me believe in myself. 

They gave me words of encouragement, started to feed me deep questions about myself so that I could see how damn strong I was. 

But we don’t always see how strong we are. Sometimes those around us see our light before we do. And that’s the beauty of this entire experience. 

I am strong, I was strong, but if I didn’t have the RIGHT people around me, I wouldn’t have made it as far, I wouldn’t have seen my potential. 

This year, surround yourself with people who see your potential, who push you, who see your strengths more that you even do at times. It can and will change your life. 

Thank you @lesia.nez & @blakebasuel 🙏

10/10 recommend trying a cold plunge 🤍 

Happy 2024 everyone 🥲❤️

Life Is Bittersweet, Remember It’s All Mental and Always Choose Happy ✨👇

My life started to truly shift when I realized that the first step in taking control of my career, fitness, relationships, income,… was taking control of my mind. 

This small shift in perspective, allows me to move in confidence every single day knowing that I am TRULY in control. I am in control of how I REACT to life’s circumstances. 

I choose who I surround myself with. 
I choose how I spend my time. 
I choose what I put in my body. 
I choose what I listen to, what I watch, and what I consume on a daily basis. 

All of these create habits. And habits are the foundation that ultimately lead to the results of our lives ✨ 

This year, set goals, but more importantly focus on setting new HABITS. Habits, are what will make or break of your goals actually become reality.
